<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Non-Disclose Agreement</title>

    <style>
      @font-face {
        font-family: 'bebas_neue_bold';
        src: url('<%= URL %>/assets/fonts/BebasNeue_Bold.ttf');
      }

      @font-face {
        font-family: 'OpenSans-Regular';
        src: url('<%= URL %>/assets/fonts/OpenSans-Regular.ttf');
      }

      @font-face {
        font-family: 'OpenSans-SemiBold';
        src: url('<%= URL %>/assets/fonts/OpenSans-SemiBold.ttf');
      }

      h1,
      h2,
      h3,
      h4,
      h5,
      h6 {
        font-family: 'bebas_neue_bold';
        color: #02528a;
      }

      ul li {
        margin-bottom: 15px;
      }

      p,
      li {
        font-family: 'OpenSans-Regular';
        font-size: 13px;
        line-height: 28px;
      }

      @page {
        /*   margin: 20px;
        size: letter; or width then height 150mm 50mm*/
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <section
      class="non_disclosure_agreement_sec"
      style="max-width: 80%; margin: 0 auto"
    >
      <div class="main_heading">
        <h1
          style="
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: #02528a;
            font-size: 16px;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 0;
          "
        >
          NON-Disclosure Agreement
        </h1>
      </div>
      <div class="secondary_heading">
        <h2
          style="
            color: #02528a;
            font-size: 16px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            text-align: center;
          "
        >
          This is a non-disclosure agreement ["Agreement"] Between:
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="agreement_header">
        <div class="left_col" style="width: 45%; float: left">
          <p style="max-width: 90%; text-align: justify">
            Business Brokerage Services, LLC a Colorado Corporation (“the
            Brokerage”).
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="center_col" style="width: 10%; float: left">
          <p style="text-align: center; font-family: 'OpenSans-SemiBold'">
            AND
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="right_col" style="width: 45%; float: left">
          <p style="max-width: 90%; text-align: justify; margin-left: auto">
            The undersigned individual and on behalf of undersigned’s business
            entity, its officers, directors, partners, shareholders, employees,
            agents, and advisors (collectively the “Buyer”)
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="agreement_header">
        <div class="left_col" style="width: 45%; float: left">
          <h3
            style="
              color: #02528a;
              font-size: 14.5px;
              text-transform: uppercase;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "
          >
            Business Brokerage Services, LLC
          </h3>
          <p style="max-width: 90%; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 15px">
            7651 Shaffer Parkway Suite B2
          </p>
          <p style="max-width: 90%; margin-top: 0">Littleton, Colorado 80127</p>
          <p style="max-width: 90%; margin-top: 0">ask@denverbbs.com</p>
        </div>
        <!-- <div class="center_col" style="width: 10%; float: left;">
                <p style="text-align: center; font-family: 'OpenSans-SemiBold';"></p>
            </div> -->
        <div class="right_col" style="width: 45%; float: right">
          <br />
          <br />
          <p style="max-width: 90%; margin-left: auto"><%= user_name %></p>
          <p style="max-width: 90%; margin-left: auto"><%= user_contact %></p>
          <p style="max-width: 90%; margin-left: auto"><%= user_email %></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="agreement_subject"
        style="width: 100%; float: left; text-align: center"
      >
        <h3
          style="
            color: #02528a;
            font-size: 14.5px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            display: inline-block;
          "
        >
          Nda For/ Business Ref :
        </h3>
        <p style="display: inline-block"><%= store_name %></p>
      </div>

      <div class="agreement_main_content" style="float: left; width: 100%">
        <p style="text-align: justify">
          Our agreement with the Seller requires that the Brokerage obtain a
          Non-Disclosure Agreement and evidence of financial ability/proof of
          funds from the Buyer before disclosing the name, location, or any
          confidential information of the Business(s). Any and all information
          obtained from the Buyer will be kept confidential by the Brokerage.
          “Information” as used in this Agreement will include the fact that the
          Business is for sale, in addition to any/all proprietary, sensitive,
          confidential data, and descriptive details provided about the
          Business(s) by the Brokerage, Seller, or any other sources. The Buyer
          agrees that ALL Information will be kept confidential.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="buyers_acknowledges_content" style="float: left; width: 100%">
        <div class="top_heading">
          <h3
            style="
              font-size: 14.5px;
              text-transform: uppercase;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "
          >
            The Buyer acknowledges and agrees:
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="acknowledge_points">
          <ul style="text-align: justify">
            <li style="color: red">
              Not to contact the Seller or it’s landlords, franchisors,
              employees, suppliers, or customers except through the Brokerage.
              All correspondence, Inquiries, offers to purchase, and
              negotiations relating to the purchase or lease of any business
              presented by the Brokerage will be conducted exclusively through
              the Brokerage.
            </li>
            <li>
              Any information provided about the Business is proprietary,
              sensitive, and confidential. The disclosure of any information to
              any other party may be damaging to the Business and/or Seller.
            </li>
            <li>
              Not to disclose, for a period of 2 years following the date of
              receipt of any information regarding any Business to any other
              person who has not signed this Agreement, except to secure the
              advice and recommendations of business advisors (accountants or
              attorneys).
            </li>
            <li>
              Not to circumvent or interfere with the Brokerage contract with
              the Seller in any way. The Buyer understands that if the Buyer or
              any agent thereof, interferes with the Brokerage's contractual
              right its fee from the Seller, the Buyer will be personally liable
              for any commission due to the Brokerage. The Buyer understands
              that shoul the Buyer become a manager, employee, or otherwise
              connected in any way with the Business shown or offered to the
              Buyer for sale, or should the Buyer buy, trade, lease or exchange
              any of the Business that is disclosed to the Buyer, then a
              commission will be due to the Brokerage from the Buyer.
            </li>
            <li>
              The Buyer understands that if the Buyer purchases the Business
              through the Brokerage, the Buyer will not be liable for
              commissions to be paid to the Brokerage by Seller.
            </li>
            <li>
              The Buyer acknowledges and agrees that all Information regarding
              the Business is provided by the Seller or other sources and is not
              verified in any way by the Brokerage. The Brokerage has knowledge
              of the accuracy of the Information and makes no warranty,
              expressed or implied, as to the accuracy of the Information.
              Understanding that the Buyer will make an independent verification
              of the Information prior to the purchase of the business, the
              Buyer agrees that the Brokerage is not responsible for the
              accuracy of any of the Information that the Buyer receives or
              fails to receive and that the Buyer agrees to indemnify and hold
              the Brokerage and its agents harmless from any claims or damages
              which may occur by reason of the inaccuracy or incompleteness of
              any Information provided to the Buyer with respect to the
              Business.
            </li>
            <li>
              Should the Buyer decide to no longer pursue the purchase of the
              Business, the Buyer will promptly advise the Brokerage of this
              fact and will immediately return all proprietary, sensitive, and
              confidential Information furnished to the Buyer, without retaining
              copies, summaries, analyses, or extracts.
            </li>
            <li>
              The Buyer further agrees that any earnest money deposit made for
              the purchase of this business will be held in trust with Business
              Brokerage Services, LLC.
            </li>
            <li>
              Business Brokerage Services is a Multiple-Person Firm that has a
              “Success Fee” based upon a contract between Seller for the sale,
              trade, lease, or transfer of the Seller's Business and/or
              Property.
            </li>
            <li>
              The Broker is a Transactional Broker/Intermediary. However, the
              Brokerage, at its sole discretion with notice, may assign
              different roles to different Brokers to assist the Buyer or Seller
              reapectively.
            </li>
            <li>
              The Buyer was provided “Brokerage Disclosure to Buyer Definitions
              of Working Relationships.”
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="working_relations_sec" style="float: left; width: 100%">
        <div class="main_heading">
          <h3
            style="
              text-transform: uppercase;
              font-size: 14.5px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "
          >
            BROKERAGE DISCLOSURE TO BUYER DEFINITIONS OF WORKING RELATIONSHIPS
          </h3>
        </div>

        <div class="working_relaton_points" style="text-align: justify">
          <div class="point">
            <p>
              <span
                style="
                  color: #02528a;
                  font-size: 14.5px;
                  text-decoration: underline;
                  font-family: 'bebas_neue_bold';
                "
                >Seller's Agent</span
              >
              A seller’s agent (or listing agent) works solely on behalf of the
              seller to promote the interests of the seller with the utmost good
              faith, loyalty and fidelity. The agent negotiates on behalf of and
              acts as an advocate for the seller. The seller’s agent must
              disclose to potential buyers all adverse material facts actually
              known by the seller’s agent about the property. A separate written
              listing agreement is required which sets forth the duties and
              obligations of the broker and the seller.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="point">
            <p>
              <span
                style="
                  color: #02528a;
                  font-size: 14.5px;
                  text-decoration: underline;
                  font-family: 'bebas_neue_bold';
                "
                >Buyer’s Agent:</span
              >
              A buyer’s agent works solely on behalf of the buyer to promote the
              interests of the buyer with the utmost good faith, loyalty and
              fidelity. The agent negotiates on behalf of and acts as an
              advocate for the buyer. The buyer’s agent must disclose to
              potential sellers all adverse material facts actually known by the
              buyer’s agent including the buyer’s financial ability to perform
              the terms of the transaction and, if a residential property,
              whether the buyer intends to occupy the property. A separate
              written buyer agency agreement is required which sets forth the
              duties and obligations of the broker and the buyer.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="point">
            <p>
              <span
                style="
                  color: #02528a;
                  font-size: 14.5px;
                  text-decoration: underline;
                  font-family: 'bebas_neue_bold';
                "
                >Transaction-Broker:</span
              >
              A transaction-broker assists the buyer or seller or both
              throughout a real estate transaction by performing terms of any
              written or oral agreement, fully informing the parties, presenting
              all offers and assisting the parties with any contracts, including
              the closing of the transaction without being an agent or advocate
              for any of the parties. A transaction-broker must use reasonable
              skill and care in the performance of any oral or written
              agreement, and must make the same disclosures as agents about all
              adverse material facts actually known by the transaction-broker
              concerning a property or a buyer’s financial ability to perform
              the terms of a transaction and, if a residential property, whether
              the buyer intends to occupy the property. No written agreement is
              required.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="point">
            <p>
              <span
                style="
                  color: #02528a;
                  font-size: 14.5px;
                  text-decoration: underline;
                  font-family: 'bebas_neue_bold';
                "
                >Customer:</span
              >
              A customer is a party to a real estate transaction with whom the
              broker has no brokerage relationship because such party has not
              engaged or employed the broker, either as the party’s agent or as
              the party’s transaction-broker.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="broker_information_sec"
        style="float: left; width: 100%; page-break-before: always"
      >
        <div class="main_heading">
          <h3
            style="
              text-transform: uppercase;
              font-size: 14.5px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
              font-family: 'OpenSans-SemiBold';
            "
          >
            BROKER INFORMATION
          </h3>
        </div>

        <div class="form_content">
          <p style="margin-top: 0">
            Are you a broker, or in contract with one?
            <span>(<%= broker_contract %> )</span>
          </p>
          <div class="col_wrapper" style="font-weight: 400">
            <div class="col_left" style="float: left; width: 48%">
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Broker's Name:</span>
                <p style="display: inline-block; margin-top: 0">
                  <%= broker_name %>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col_right" style="float: right; width: 48%">
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Broker's Company Name:</span>
                <p style="display: inline-block; margin-top: 0">
                  <%= brokers_company_name %>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p style="color: #02528a; float: left">
            If you selected yes above, broker name and broker's company name is
            mandatory.
          </p>

          <div class="main_heading" style="float: left; width: 100%">
            <h3
              style="
                text-transform: uppercase;
                font-size: 14.5px;
                margin-bottom: 15px;
                font-family: 'OpenSans-SemiBold';
              "
            >
              PERSONAL INFORMATION [OPTIONAL]
            </h3>
          </div>

          <div class="col_wrapper">
            <div
              class="col_left"
              style="float: left; width: 48%; font-weight: 400"
            >
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Street Address:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0"><%= street_address %></p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">State:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0"><%= state %></p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Location Preferences:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0"><%= location_preference %></p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Current Occupation:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0"><%= current_occupation %></p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Business Allocation Time:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0">
                  <%= allocation_time_towards_business %>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div
              class="col_right"
              style="float: right; width: 48%; font-weight: 400"
            >
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">City:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0"><%= city %></p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Zip Code:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0"><%= zipcode %></p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Capital For Purchase:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0"><%= capital_available_purchase %></p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Type Of Busniess:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0"><%= type_of_business %></p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span style="color: #02528a">Min Annual Income Needs:</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 0"><%= minimum_annual_income_needs %></p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="acknowledgment_check" style="float: left; width: 100%">
            <p>
              By proceeding, you agree that Business Brokerage Services may
              communicate with you via telephone, video, email, text messages,
              or other media and messaging applications. Message and data rates
              may apply. If you would like to opt out at any time, please send
              an email with "STOP" to ask@denverbbs.com.
            </p>
            <p>
              I Acknowledge That I Have Read The Non-Disclosure Agreement And
              Brokerage Disclosure To Buyer Definitions Of Working Relationships
              Carefully And Fully Understand Them.
              <span style="font-weight: 800">( <%= acknowleged_check %> )</span>
            </p>
            <p>
              I Unconditionally Agree To All Terms And Conditions Of All The
              Points Above
              <span style="font-weight: 800"
                >( <%= terms_condition_check %> )</span
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="footer_text"
            style="
              text-align: center;
              float: left;
              width: 100%;
              margin-top: 20px;
            "
          >
            <p style="font-family: 'OpenSans-SemiBold'">
              All Personal Information Received From Buyer Is Confidential And
              Shall Not Be Shared With Any Other Entities
            </p>
            <br />
            <br />
            <p style="font-family: 'OpenSans-SemiBold'">
              Submitted by <%= user_name %> from the email address: <%=
              user_email %> on <%= signing_date %> from Ip Address: <%= ip %>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
